01:30:35.805 --> 01:30:38.433
Baker, Schwedes,
they're good backs.

01:30:41.436 --> 01:30:44.064
But no sense in
getting hurt worse, right?

01:30:47.400 --> 01:30:50.028
Entering the fourth
quarter of play,

01:30:50.111 --> 01:30:53.907
the tension level here
at the Cotton Bowl
is palpable.

01:30:54.574 --> 01:30:56.993
We let them
right back in the game.

01:30:59.454 --> 01:31:01.706
Coach, Davis.

01:31:03.249 --> 01:31:05.418
All right, boys,
keep your heads in the game.
Don't worry about it.

01:31:05.502 --> 01:31:06.711
Ernie, what are you doing?

01:31:06.795 --> 01:31:08.505
I need to talk to you, Coach.
I need you to ice that leg.

01:31:08.588 --> 01:31:10.131
I already have.
I need to talk
to you for a sec.

01:31:10.215 --> 01:31:11.925
No, no, you are not playing.
Just listen to me for a sec.

01:31:12.008 --> 01:31:13.009
You can watch,
but you cannot play.

01:31:13.093 --> 01:31:15.095
Just hear me out, Coach.

01:31:16.638 --> 01:31:20.934
Coach, on the trip down here
I saw a lot of things
out that bus window.

01:31:21.017 --> 01:31:23.228
Now, we get to Dallas,
they got me, Jack and Art

01:31:23.311 --> 01:31:25.188
in a tiny room with cots.

01:31:25.271 --> 01:31:27.982
We can't use the elevator
'cause we might
scare the white folks.

01:31:28.066 --> 01:31:30.944
Can't even walk in
the front door of a hotel.

01:31:32.612 --> 01:31:35.031
Now, all those people
who did that,

01:31:35.115 --> 01:31:37.492
who believe that's right,
are watching.

01:31:42.622 --> 01:31:44.958
But you know what,
so are they.

01:31:45.041 --> 01:31:46.960
(CHEERING)

01:31:52.006 --> 01:31:53.258
(SIGHS)

01:31:55.969 --> 01:31:56.928
Can you even run?

01:31:57.011 --> 01:31:58.054
Yes, sir.

01:31:58.138 --> 01:31:59.514
I don't want to
hurt you anymore.

01:31:59.597 --> 01:32:01.141
I'm ready.

01:32:03.685 --> 01:32:05.228
All right.

01:32:05.311 --> 01:32:08.148
Strong load right,
42 shovel pass.

01:32:08.231 --> 01:32:10.066
Go.
Let's go, Ernie.

01:32:10.525 --> 01:32:15.155
And now the 76,000 fans
at the Cotton Bowl
are stunned!

01:32:15.405 --> 01:32:19.576
<i>ANNOUNCER: Ernie Davis</i>
<i>has returned</i>
<i>to the playing field.</i>

01:32:22.162 --> 01:32:23.204
Let's go.

01:32:23.288 --> 01:32:24.706
Man, that's Ernie Davis!

01:32:24.789 --> 01:32:25.874
(ALL CHEERING)

01:32:28.626 --> 01:32:29.627
LUNDY: Strong left.

01:32:29.711 --> 01:32:32.130
SARETTE: Six regular!
Six regular! Tight.

01:32:32.213 --> 01:32:35.925
<i>ANNOUNCER: The Orangemen,
ball on their
own 40-yard line,</i>

01:32:36.009 --> 01:32:37.427
<i>are desperate
for a first down</i>

01:32:37.510 --> 01:32:39.721
<i>to keep the ball
out of the hands</i>

01:32:39.804 --> 01:32:42.766
<i>of Longhorn quarterback
Bobby Lackey.</i>

01:32:44.267 --> 01:32:46.019
<i>And the ball comes loose.</i>

01:32:47.395 --> 01:32:49.147
<i>Texas has recovered.</i>

01:32:49.230 --> 01:32:50.565
His knee was down, ref.

01:32:50.648 --> 01:32:51.691
First down, Texas!

01:32:51.775 --> 01:32:52.901
Bad call, ref.

01:32:52.984 --> 01:32:54.402
My knee was down, sir.

01:32:54.527 --> 01:32:57.614
They're trying to
steal it from us.
I was down.

01:32:57.697 --> 01:33:00.742
Franklin, Franklin,
get in there for Davis, go.

01:33:00.825 --> 01:33:03.411
No. Get back.
I'm staying in.
I'm staying in.

01:33:03.495 --> 01:33:04.871
Regulations!

01:33:07.874 --> 01:33:13.296
<i>ANNOUNCER: Texas on
the 40-yard line with the ball
and with the game's momentum.</i>

01:33:13.379 --> 01:33:16.925
<i>Bobby Lackey
drops back to pass.</i>

01:33:17.008 --> 01:33:20.887
<i>Throws down fie Id,</i>
<i>he's got a receiver open.</i>

01:33:24.933 --> 01:33:26.434
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:33:26.518 --> 01:33:27.477
Go! Go!

01:33:27.560 --> 01:33:28.895
All the way!
All the way!

01:33:32.732 --> 01:33:35.693
That's the way.
Offense, offense,
let's go!

01:33:35.777 --> 01:33:37.070
Let's take advantage.

01:33:37.862 --> 01:33:39.864
BEN: Get out there. Let's go!

01:33:42.158 --> 01:33:45.245
<i>ANNOUNCER: First down,
10 yards to go from the 13.</i>

01:33:46.246 --> 01:33:48.164
<i>Syracuse has to
move the chains</i>

01:33:48.248 --> 01:33:50.291
<i>and keep the clock
ticking down</i>

01:33:50.375 --> 01:33:53.419
<i>or put this game away
with another touchdown.</i>

01:33:53.753 --> 01:33:55.088
SARETTE: Hut one.

01:34:07.475 --> 01:34:09.018
Yeah! Yeah, go, go, go!

01:34:09.102 --> 01:34:10.562
He's behind you. Go!

01:34:10.645 --> 01:34:12.397
That's it! That's it.

01:34:21.114 --> 01:34:22.782
He got this. Go!

01:34:40.758 --> 01:34:43.052
<i>ANNOUNCER: An</i>
<i>unbelievable play!</i>

01:34:43.136 --> 01:34:45.221
Ernie Davis scoring

01:34:45.305 --> 01:34:50.310
on an amazing
87-yard catch and run!

01:34:50.476 --> 01:34:51.769
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:35:03.781 --> 01:35:05.867
<i>With the final seconds
ticking away...</i>

01:35:05.950 --> 01:35:07.035
Stay in the game.

01:35:07.118 --> 01:35:08.745
Stay in the game.
It's not over.

01:35:08.828 --> 01:35:11.497
<i>...the Longhorns are looking
to tie this game up</i>

01:35:11.581 --> 01:35:14.334
<i>with a last chance
shot at the end zone.</i>

01:35:30.391 --> 01:35:31.935
(ALL CHEERING)

01:35:48.952 --> 01:35:50.370
(INAUDIBLE)

01:36:15.103 --> 01:36:19.649
All right, ladies, settle
down. Settle down. Give me
your undivided attention. Hey!

01:36:19.732 --> 01:36:21.734
It's just been announced,

01:36:22.402 --> 01:36:26.614
the 1960 Cotton Bowl
MVP. Congratulations
to Mr. Ernie Davis.

01:36:26.698 --> 01:36:28.241
(ALL CHEERING)

01:36:29.951 --> 01:36:31.577
Ernie!
Congrats.

01:36:32.370 --> 01:36:33.705
Come here.

01:36:34.831 --> 01:36:36.624
Congratulations, brother.

01:36:36.708 --> 01:36:38.543
All right,
everybody,
listen up.

01:36:38.626 --> 01:36:41.295
This gentleman
wants to say something.

01:36:42.880 --> 01:36:44.173
Go ahead.

01:36:46.467 --> 01:36:51.848
What the man is trying
to say is that the trophy
ceremony in our honor

01:36:51.931 --> 01:36:54.600
will be held at Oak Hill
Country Club tonight.

01:36:54.684 --> 01:36:56.144
Great.
Very nice.

01:36:56.227 --> 01:37:00.189
Unfortunately,
the Oak Hill Country Club
is color restricted.

01:37:01.566 --> 01:37:02.859
Which means
that three of us,

01:37:02.942 --> 01:37:07.947
including the player who was
awarded the Cotton Bowl MVP
today, cannot attend.

01:37:08.281 --> 01:37:09.282
(ALL GROANING)

01:37:09.365 --> 01:37:10.533
PLAYER: Seriously?

01:37:10.616 --> 01:37:11.743
Ridiculous.

01:37:15.621 --> 01:37:17.957
Now, how do we
feel about that?

01:37:18.624 --> 01:37:20.543
I don't know about you,

01:37:21.127 --> 01:37:24.380
but I hear they have
some great barbecue
down here.

01:37:24.464 --> 01:37:26.090
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

01:37:30.803 --> 01:37:32.972
(BAND PLAYING
ROCK 'N' ROLL MUSIC)

01:37:34.265 --> 01:37:35.683
<i>(SINGING)</i>

01:38:03.169 --> 01:38:05.630
(ALL CHEERING)

01:38:16.724 --> 01:38:18.267
(ALL WHOOPING)

01:38:54.679 --> 01:38:56.097
You read it.

01:38:59.058 --> 01:39:02.812
"To Syracuse University
department of athletics.

01:39:03.229 --> 01:39:06.232
"This is to inform
you that Ernest Davis

01:39:06.315 --> 01:39:10.069
"has been selected
as one of the three
finalists for the..."

01:39:13.739 --> 01:39:15.116
(CHUCKLES)

01:39:16.200 --> 01:39:18.119
Congratulations, Ernie.

01:39:22.832 --> 01:39:25.126
MAN: We're ready
for you, Mr. Davis.

01:39:29.755 --> 01:39:31.048
<i>MAN </i><i>ON MIC:</i>
<i>...or witnessed
more closely...</i>

01:39:31.132 --> 01:39:32.508
Good luck, Mr. Davis.

01:39:32.592 --> 01:39:33.759
Thank you, sir.

01:39:33.843 --> 01:39:39.348
<i>...the importance of the
gridiron or effected more
change in the game...</i>

01:39:39.432 --> 01:39:44.395
<i>...than John W. Heisman.
So, it is with distinct
pleasure...</i>

01:39:45.104 --> 01:39:46.981
No matter what
happens up there,

01:39:47.064 --> 01:39:49.025
I want you to know
that I'm really
proud of you, son.

01:39:49.108 --> 01:39:51.944
<i>...the memorial</i>
<i>trophy bearing his name.</i>

01:39:52.028 --> 01:39:56.616
<i>The first is Ernest R. Davis
from Syracuse University.</i>

01:40:04.540 --> 01:40:08.669
<i>Our next nominee
is Robert Ferguson,
Ohio State University.</i>

01:40:11.339 --> 01:40:16.052
<i>Our third nominee</i>
<i>is James Saxton,</i>
<i>the University of Texas.</i>

01:40:17.428 --> 01:40:18.387
Congratulations.

01:40:18.471 --> 01:40:20.556
Thanks, man.

01:40:24.060 --> 01:40:25.895
<i>The Heisman Trophy has,</i>

01:40:25.978 --> 01:40:31.317
<i>since 1935, represented
everything that is great
about collegiate athletics.</i>

01:40:31.400 --> 01:40:37.114
<i>And these three fine young
men represent their teams,
their schools</i>

01:40:37.406 --> 01:40:39.617
<i>and their families
with honor.</i>

01:40:40.034 --> 01:40:43.204
<i>The voting for</i>
<i>this year's award was</i>
<i>the closest in history</i>

01:40:43.287 --> 01:40:46.040
<i>and each of these
players is deserving.</i>

01:40:46.123 --> 01:40:51.295
<i>That said, the winner
of this year's Heisman
Memorial Trophy is</i>

01:40:55.841 --> 01:40:58.970
<i>Ernest R. Davis from
Syracuse University.</i>

01:40:59.887 --> 01:41:01.472
(EXCLAIMING)

01:41:10.314 --> 01:41:11.357
Congratulations.

01:41:11.440 --> 01:41:12.441
Thank you.

01:41:14.360 --> 01:41:15.653
Congratulations.

01:41:15.736 --> 01:41:17.029
I appreciate it.

01:41:19.073 --> 01:41:20.992
Congratulations, Ernie.
Thank you.

01:41:21.075 --> 01:41:22.618
You did great.

01:41:29.917 --> 01:41:31.210
(EXHALES)

01:41:34.088 --> 01:41:37.133
<i>First, I'd like to thank
the Heisman committee.</i>

01:41:40.386 --> 01:41:41.554
<i>Sarah,</i>

01:41:42.722 --> 01:41:44.056
<i>my family,</i>

01:41:44.974 --> 01:41:46.350
<i>Mom,</i>

01:41:47.226 --> 01:41:48.352
<i>Will,</i>

01:41:52.565 --> 01:41:53.733
<i>and...</i>

01:41:55.401 --> 01:41:58.738
<i>And Pops for
believing in me.</i>

01:41:59.947 --> 01:42:02.908
<i>And Jim Brown
for letting me
wear his number.</i>

01:42:02.992 --> 01:42:04.493
(PEOPLE CHUCKLING)

01:42:08.247 --> 01:42:12.001
<i>I'd also like to</i>
<i>thank my head coach,</i>
<i>Ben Schwartzwalder,</i>

01:42:13.711 --> 01:42:18.215
<i>for making me better,
being a good teacher,</i>

01:42:19.717 --> 01:42:21.844
<i>and for being a good man.</i>

01:42:27.224 --> 01:42:29.018
<i>Thank you, everyone.</i>

01:42:46.786 --> 01:42:48.371
Where exactly
are we going?

01:42:48.454 --> 01:42:49.747
Right this way.

01:43:03.135 --> 01:43:07.640
Ernie, I was in town
and I wanted to get
a chance to meet you.

01:43:08.182 --> 01:43:11.977
I know today is a proud
day for you. You've really
accomplished something here.

01:43:12.061 --> 01:43:13.062
Congratulations.

01:43:13.145 --> 01:43:14.980
Thank you, Mr. President.

01:43:17.316 --> 01:43:18.818
<i>MAN: Fourth down, 9 yards.</i>

01:43:19.735 --> 01:43:23.781
Must be nice having
the number one draft
pick, huh, George?

01:43:23.864 --> 01:43:26.158
I'm sure Ernie Davis
is a fine boy,

01:43:26.242 --> 01:43:31.163
but I'll start signing Negroes
when the Harlem Globetrotters
start signing whites.

01:43:32.248 --> 01:43:35.918
Mr. Modell, George Marshall
from the Washington
Redskins is on the phone.

01:43:36.001 --> 01:43:37.628
Of course he is.

01:43:38.504 --> 01:43:41.340
George, what
a surprise to
hear from you.

01:43:42.508 --> 01:43:45.136
You do?
Okay, I'm listening.

01:43:46.512 --> 01:43:47.763
LAWYER: It's all
over the wire.

01:43:47.847 --> 01:43:50.724
The Redskins just traded their
number one pick to Cleveland.

01:43:50.808 --> 01:43:52.184
You're a commodity now.

01:43:52.268 --> 01:43:55.980
Yeah, you should listen to
your lawyer, man. He's right.
It's all business now.

01:43:56.063 --> 01:43:57.606
Have you been sick recently?

01:43:57.690 --> 01:43:59.442
No, I feel great.

01:44:00.443 --> 01:44:03.654
I may be a commodity,
but this commodity is
playing for Cleveland.

01:44:03.737 --> 01:44:06.449
Me and Jim Brown in
the same backfield.

01:44:06.532 --> 01:44:09.076
You're gonna steal
his number again?

01:44:22.590 --> 01:44:24.175
ERNIE: Oh! Oh!

01:44:24.758 --> 01:44:26.135
Stop it.

01:44:31.223 --> 01:44:32.516
I don't want to leave.

01:44:32.600 --> 01:44:33.851
You don't have to leave.

01:44:33.934 --> 01:44:35.102
I do.

01:44:36.228 --> 01:44:38.355
I should bring you with me.

01:44:39.064 --> 01:44:42.151
Just jump in my suitcase.
You know you can fit.

01:44:43.444 --> 01:44:44.528
Oh!

01:44:45.237 --> 01:44:46.864
Oh, no.
Oh, I slipped.

01:44:47.448 --> 01:44:48.824
I'm sorry.

01:44:53.204 --> 01:44:55.206
That was a mistake,
too. I'm sorry.
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

01:44:55.289 --> 01:44:57.249
I have to get
you a new blouse.

01:45:00.586 --> 01:45:02.004
Look at you.

01:45:04.965 --> 01:45:06.217
What are you doing?

01:45:06.300 --> 01:45:07.551
He's at the 10.

01:45:08.636 --> 01:45:11.013
(SARAH LAUGHING)
The 20, the 30...

01:45:13.182 --> 01:45:14.183
The 40...

01:45:14.266 --> 01:45:15.643
(EXCLAIMING)

01:45:20.523 --> 01:45:22.691
Is that another
nose bleed?

01:45:32.493 --> 01:45:34.036
You know,
Hound Dog says he
gets hit so hard,

01:45:34.119 --> 01:45:38.040
he wakes up with blood on
his pillow. Doesn't even
know where it came from.

01:45:38.123 --> 01:45:40.125
But you haven't been hit.

01:45:43.003 --> 01:45:45.548
Ernie, you haven't
been hit. What...

01:45:46.382 --> 01:45:49.134
Bus leaves for practice
in a half hour.

01:45:51.262 --> 01:45:53.055
Be here when I get back?

01:45:53.138 --> 01:45:54.139
I'll be here.

01:46:07.486 --> 01:46:08.904
Right two to Maury,
right two to Maury.

01:46:08.988 --> 01:46:10.322
QUARTERBACK: Set? Go!

01:46:16.829 --> 01:46:18.455
MAN 1: Stop.
MAN 2: Change your block,
change your block.

01:46:18.539 --> 01:46:23.252
Behind me,
the East team led by
Syracuse's Ben Schwartzwalder.

01:46:23.335 --> 01:46:25.212
Ernie Davis goes
through the paces

01:46:25.296 --> 01:46:28.465
in preparation
for Saturday night's
All-America game.

01:46:31.427 --> 01:46:33.679
ASSISTANT COACH:
Davis look a little
sluggish to you?

01:46:33.762 --> 01:46:35.723
He'll be fine.

01:46:35.806 --> 01:46:37.433
QUARTERBACK: Tight right,
34 wide dig. Ready?

01:46:37.516 --> 01:46:38.892
PLAYER: Come on!
ALL: Break!

01:46:40.811 --> 01:46:41.979
QUARTERBACK: Okie. Okie.

01:46:42.062 --> 01:46:44.106
Watch. Strong left.
Strong left!

01:46:44.189 --> 01:46:45.357
PLAYER: Right!

01:46:45.608 --> 01:46:47.401
(PANTING)

01:46:47.484 --> 01:46:49.987
QUARTERBACK: Six box!
Six box! Set!

01:46:52.531 --> 01:46:53.991
Hut! Hut!

01:47:01.790 --> 01:47:03.375
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

01:47:07.171 --> 01:47:09.923
All right, let's run
it again. Let's go.

01:47:11.800 --> 01:47:14.762
It's all right.
You'll get them
next time. Come on.

01:47:15.804 --> 01:47:17.056
(PANTING)

01:47:35.074 --> 01:47:36.241
Ernie?

01:47:37.159 --> 01:47:38.744
Ernie? You okay?

01:47:53.384 --> 01:47:55.386
(INAUDIBLE)

01:48:09.441 --> 01:48:12.778
He's got to have another
transfusion. He's lost
quite a lot of blood.

01:48:12.861 --> 01:48:14.530
How'd he do that?
We're not sure.

01:48:14.613 --> 01:48:16.407
He's gonna need
further tests.

01:48:16.490 --> 01:48:18.534
So test.
Gentlemen.

01:48:21.161 --> 01:48:22.413
(SIGHS)

01:48:23.163 --> 01:48:25.999
Now what am I
supposed to
tell the press?

01:48:28.085 --> 01:48:29.628
Mumps.
What?

01:48:30.671 --> 01:48:33.215
He's got a bad
case of the mumps.

01:48:33.298 --> 01:48:34.717
That's good.

01:48:34.800 --> 01:48:36.635
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

01:48:37.469 --> 01:48:40.472
QUARTERBACK: Double tight!
Double tight! Down!

01:48:44.184 --> 01:48:45.394
Set!

01:48:45.477 --> 01:48:47.062
(PANTING)

01:48:47.146 --> 01:48:49.189
Blue 3-21!

01:48:49.273 --> 01:48:51.066
Blue 3-21!

01:48:51.150 --> 01:48:52.443
Hut! Hut!

01:49:04.496 --> 01:49:05.831
(PANTING)

01:49:10.419 --> 01:49:12.004
(WHISTLE BLOWS)

01:49:14.465 --> 01:49:16.258
ASSISTANT COACH: Hey, Ernie!

01:49:17.843 --> 01:49:19.845
The man wants to see you.

01:49:22.431 --> 01:49:24.516
PLAYER 1: All right,
get back.
PLAYER 2: Let's go.

01:49:27.853 --> 01:49:28.812
Hey.

01:49:28.896 --> 01:49:29.938
Hey, Mr. Modell.

01:49:30.022 --> 01:49:31.023
Hey.
How are you?

01:49:31.106 --> 01:49:32.149
I'm good. I've been
watching you.

01:49:33.692 --> 01:49:35.152
You know,
new system and all.
Yeah, listen, Ernie.

01:49:35.235 --> 01:49:36.528
All I need is some rest.
Yeah, the system is...

01:49:36.612 --> 01:49:37.613
Once I get used to it...

01:49:37.696 --> 01:49:39.072
All right.
Ernie, Ernie, Ernie,

01:49:39.156 --> 01:49:41.617
I spoke with
Dr. Hewlett and...

01:49:42.701 --> 01:49:47.039
Look, he doesn't know
what it is, but they know
something's not right, Ernie.

01:49:47.664 --> 01:49:52.252
I should have told you
earlier, kid. I really
can't clear you for practice.

01:49:52.878 --> 01:49:55.589
If I can't practice,
how am I gonna play?

01:49:56.006 --> 01:49:59.593
You're not gonna
play. Not now.

01:49:59.968 --> 01:50:03.514
And maybe not
this season.

01:50:09.019 --> 01:50:10.312
(SIGHS)

01:50:10.521 --> 01:50:12.731
(STAMMERS) Well, when?

01:50:14.441 --> 01:50:15.943
I don't know.

01:50:17.194 --> 01:50:19.196
I don't know, kid.

01:50:19.279 --> 01:50:22.199
Get better, okay?
Your job is to get well.

01:50:22.282 --> 01:50:25.536
Mr. Modell,
you don't understand.

01:50:26.578 --> 01:50:29.331
Everything I got is
because of football.

01:50:33.001 --> 01:50:34.837
I need to play.

01:50:34.920 --> 01:50:35.921
Yeah.

01:50:36.004 --> 01:50:38.924
Mr. Modell, please, sir.

01:50:40.926 --> 01:50:44.888
Next year, kid.
We're counting on you
next year. Really.

01:51:03.115 --> 01:51:04.575
(PANTING)

01:51:34.438 --> 01:51:35.814
Thank you.

01:51:37.357 --> 01:51:38.984
Thank you, sir.

01:51:40.152 --> 01:51:42.988
Did you hear
back from the
teaching job yet?

01:51:45.115 --> 01:51:46.074
Well?

01:51:46.158 --> 01:51:47.659
They offered it to me.

01:51:48.243 --> 01:51:49.745
That's great.

01:51:50.329 --> 01:51:51.830
I told them I had
to think about it.

01:51:51.914 --> 01:51:53.790
What's to think about?

01:51:53.874 --> 01:51:57.210
The distance between
Cleveland and
Oakland for one.

01:51:58.629 --> 01:51:59.922
Take it.

01:52:01.256 --> 01:52:02.382
What?

01:52:03.634 --> 01:52:05.719
Take the job, Sarah.

01:52:05.802 --> 01:52:08.138
You've always said
you want to do something
with your life.

01:52:08.221 --> 01:52:10.933
You didn't just
come to school
just to find a husband.

01:52:11.016 --> 01:52:14.102
You're beautiful, smart.

01:52:15.562 --> 01:52:17.522
Stick to that dream.

01:52:19.316 --> 01:52:21.318
How sick are you, Ernie?

01:52:24.529 --> 01:52:25.948
Look at me.

01:52:34.414 --> 01:52:35.707
Sarah...

01:52:37.292 --> 01:52:38.710
MAN: Ernie Davis?

01:52:39.336 --> 01:52:44.132
I hate to disturb you,
but would you sign an
autograph for my son?

01:52:44.216 --> 01:52:46.927
He's 12, and you're
his favorite player.

01:52:48.470 --> 01:52:51.348
Gonna be great to see
you with the Browns.

01:52:56.728 --> 01:52:57.688
Thank you.

01:52:57.771 --> 01:52:58.897
You're welcome.

01:53:09.408 --> 01:53:10.701
<i>Leukemia.</i>

01:53:13.245 --> 01:53:17.749
<i>It's a word that
jumps out at you.</i>

01:53:19.251 --> 01:53:21.920
<i>/ know when
I first heard
it myself,</i>

01:53:23.171 --> 01:53:24.423
<i>/ was...</i>

01:53:24.881 --> 01:53:26.383
<i>/ was scared.</i>

01:53:27.592 --> 01:53:30.178
<i>But I got a lot of
people In my corner,</i>

01:53:31.847 --> 01:53:33.265
<i>good people,</i>

01:53:35.142 --> 01:53:36.935
<i>standing beside me.</i>

01:53:38.812 --> 01:53:41.023
<i>My doctors are confident.</i>

01:53:41.523 --> 01:53:44.651
<i>They tell me</i>
<i>I'm responding well</i>
<i>to my treatment.</i>

01:53:45.444 --> 01:53:48.363
<i>So, things are good.</i>

01:53:51.867 --> 01:53:55.954
<i>And you know me.
I'm an optimist.
I'm gonna fight it.</i>

01:53:57.789 --> 01:54:02.169
<i>/ hope to get on that
field and see you all in
that press box real soon.</i>

01:54:03.628 --> 01:54:04.963
<i>Real soon.</i>

01:54:07.049 --> 01:54:08.967
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

01:54:13.764 --> 01:54:16.641
Mr. Davis, Tom Martin,
<i>Saturday Evening Post.</i>

01:54:16.725 --> 01:54:18.643
I saw you play
in the Cotton Bowl
two years ago.

01:54:18.727 --> 01:54:19.728
Okay.

01:54:19.811 --> 01:54:22.522
I'm wondering if you'd like
to write an article for us.

01:54:22.606 --> 01:54:24.024
You want me to
write an article?

01:54:24.107 --> 01:54:25.609
<i>/ don't know whether
you know this,</i>

01:54:25.692 --> 01:54:29.279
<i>but you're an inspiration
to a lot of our readers.</i>

01:54:35.452 --> 01:54:38.038
There he is,
number 77.

01:54:38.121 --> 01:54:39.831
He's as good as me?

01:54:41.208 --> 01:54:42.709
Maybe better.

01:54:58.100 --> 01:54:59.518
BEN: Hey, Ernie.

01:55:00.352 --> 01:55:02.521
Ernie, this is Floyd Little.
Floyd, this is...

01:55:02.604 --> 01:55:04.439
Ernie Davis.

01:55:04.523 --> 01:55:07.442
2,386 yards,
360 carries,

01:55:07.526 --> 01:55:09.444
6.6 yards a carry.

01:55:09.528 --> 01:55:10.862
You good at math, huh?

01:55:10.946 --> 01:55:12.322
(CHUCKLES)

01:55:19.579 --> 01:55:23.125
FLOYD: You see, my plan
is to be just like you,

01:55:24.126 --> 01:55:27.003
best Negro running
back in the NCAA,

01:55:27.087 --> 01:55:29.506
Heisman Trophy
all the way.

01:55:29.589 --> 01:55:31.883
Then the NFL,
make some money.

01:55:32.217 --> 01:55:33.635
(LAUGHING)

01:55:33.718 --> 01:55:36.388
You got it
all figured out,
don't you?

01:55:48.191 --> 01:55:51.027
What kind of bottle
do you think this is?

01:55:51.695 --> 01:55:53.822
Don't know.
Don't have a label.

01:55:53.905 --> 01:55:54.906
Right.

01:55:55.907 --> 01:55:58.034
It could be a soda bottle,

01:55:58.118 --> 01:56:00.162
it could be a beer bottle,
it could be anything.

01:56:00.245 --> 01:56:01.538
No label.

01:56:03.290 --> 01:56:06.585
You see, I never set out to be
the best Negro running back.

01:56:06.668 --> 01:56:08.879
I just wanted to be
the best running back.

01:56:08.962 --> 01:56:11.756
The best football player
I could be. Period.

01:56:13.592 --> 01:56:15.594
Look, now I'm...

01:56:21.892 --> 01:56:24.769
Floyd, I'm never gonna
play for Cleveland.

01:56:27.939 --> 01:56:29.691
Or any other team.

01:56:31.818 --> 01:56:34.404
My playing days are over.

01:56:37.115 --> 01:56:40.035
So don't you look
at that poster of me
on your wall and tell me

01:56:40.118 --> 01:56:43.288
you want to be like me,
because that isn't enough.

01:56:43.830 --> 01:56:46.666
You're gonna have to
do better than that.

01:56:49.211 --> 01:56:50.962
You think you can?

01:56:52.631 --> 01:56:53.965
Yes, sir.

01:56:57.302 --> 01:56:58.428
Good.

01:57:00.639 --> 01:57:05.310
But the thing is,
I told Notre Dame
I would sign with them.

01:57:05.894 --> 01:57:07.145
(EXCLAIMS SOFTLY)

01:57:09.814 --> 01:57:13.610
Floyd,
you know how Notre Dame
loves their passing game.

01:57:13.693 --> 01:57:16.071
My fear is a talented
runner like yourself

01:57:16.154 --> 01:57:18.990
may get stuck polishing
that Notre Dame bench
with your butt.

01:57:19.074 --> 01:57:20.867
You don't want that.

01:57:30.335 --> 01:57:34.673
(PLAYERS EXCLAIMING)

01:57:56.403 --> 01:57:57.862
(DOOR OPENS)

01:58:01.199 --> 01:58:03.410
I want to know something.

01:58:03.493 --> 01:58:04.619
Coach?

01:58:04.703 --> 01:58:07.497
What the hell did you
say to Floyd Little?

01:58:07.580 --> 01:58:09.124
(SIGHS) Why? What happened?

01:58:09.207 --> 01:58:12.127
Well, I'll be damned,
he backed out on Notre Dame.

01:58:12.210 --> 01:58:14.170
He's coming to Syracuse.

01:58:15.547 --> 01:58:18.967
Well, let's see.
I told him you like
your runners lazy,

01:58:19.884 --> 01:58:21.303
and you like players
who backtalk.

01:58:21.386 --> 01:58:22.554
Mmm-hmm.

01:58:22.637 --> 01:58:24.180
Anything else?

01:58:28.018 --> 01:58:30.437
I told him you
were a good coach.

01:58:33.606 --> 01:58:34.649
(SIGHS)

01:58:34.733 --> 01:58:36.484
I'm not gonna
lie to him, Ernie,

01:58:36.568 --> 01:58:39.154
because I know
how hard it's
gonna be for him.

01:58:39.237 --> 01:58:41.614
And I promise,
if he works hard,

01:58:43.074 --> 01:58:47.162
he can run for that end zone
whether he's in Boston
or Mississippi.

01:58:49.914 --> 01:58:53.251
And I won't tell him
that he's the next
Ernie Davis,

01:58:54.127 --> 01:58:57.088
because there won't
be another Ernie Davis.

01:59:13.938 --> 01:59:18.234
Can you believe they
suited me up to run on
the field and take a bow?

01:59:20.153 --> 01:59:21.363
I'll be right
here with you, son.

01:59:21.446 --> 01:59:22.572
<i>ANNOUNCER: Please
welcome to the field,</i>

01:59:22.655 --> 01:59:28.328
<i>number 45, from Syracuse
at halfback, Ernie Davis.</i>

01:59:28.411 --> 01:59:30.663
(CROWD CHEERING)

01:59:37.045 --> 01:59:40.256
<i>ERNIE: Mr. Martin,
in the end it turns
out you did me a favor</i>

01:59:40.340 --> 01:59:43.301
<i>when you asked me to
write this for </i> The Post.

01:59:46.888 --> 01:59:49.557
<i>You see, yesterday
was my 23rd birthday,</i>

01:59:49.641 --> 01:59:54.396
<i>and compared to some, that
doesn't seem like a whole
lot of life to talk about.</i>

02:00:00.110 --> 02:00:04.364
<i>Thing is, I don't
know how much more
is in front of me.</i>

02:00:04.447 --> 02:00:08.410
<i>And as you see from
the number of pages,
if you've read this far,</i>

02:00:08.493 --> 02:00:12.956
<i>/ did have a few things
to say, and I'm not sure
how to end this</i>

02:00:13.039 --> 02:00:14.999
<i>or even if I want to.</i>

02:00:16.209 --> 02:00:20.338
<i>It's funny. Most people
think my life has been
all about football.</i>

02:00:21.798 --> 02:00:24.050
<i>I've even thought
that myself.</i>

02:00:24.759 --> 02:00:26.886
<i>But football Is just a game.</i>

02:00:27.804 --> 02:00:30.223
<i>What matters is
what you play for.</i>

02:00:37.856 --> 02:00:42.026
<i>Sometimes, when the game
is close and everything
is on the line,</i>

02:00:42.110 --> 02:00:45.196
<i>that's when you
forget the crowd
and the noise.</i>

02:00:46.865 --> 02:00:51.536
<i>That's when it's just you
against somebody else to
see who is the better man.</i>

02:00:52.620 --> 02:00:55.039
<i>That's what
I like about
the game.</i>

02:00:55.707 --> 02:00:58.793
<i>Because at that
moment you are friends</i>

02:01:00.545 --> 02:01:02.255
<i>and you are enemies</i>

02:01:05.049 --> 02:01:06.885
<i>and you are brothers.</i>
